22namespace webrtc {
23
24class RtpPacketizerH265 : public RtpPacketizer {
25 public:
26 // Initialize with payload from encoder.
27 // The payload_data must be exactly one encoded H.265 frame.
28 RtpPacketizerH265(rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> payload,
29 PayloadSizeLimits limits,
30 H265PacketizationMode packetization_mode);
31
32 ~RtpPacketizerH265() override;
33
34 size_t NumPackets() const override;
35
36 // Get the next payload with H.265 payload header.
37 // buffer is a pointer to where the output will be written.
38 // bytes_to_send is an output variable that will contain number of bytes
39 // written to buffer. The parameter last_packet is true for the last packet of
40 // the frame, false otherwise (i.e., call the function again to get the
41 // next packet).
42 // Returns true on success or false if there was no payload to packetize.
43 bool NextPacket(RtpPacketToSend* rtp_packet) override;
44
45 private:
46 struct Packet {
47 Packet(size_t offset,
48 size_t size,
49 bool first_fragment,
50 bool last_fragment,
51 bool aggregated,
52 uint16_t header)
53 : offset(offset),
54 size(size),
55 first_fragment(first_fragment),
56 last_fragment(last_fragment),
57 aggregated(aggregated),
58 header(header) {}
59
60 size_t offset;
61 size_t size;
62 bool first_fragment;
63 bool last_fragment;
64 bool aggregated;
65 uint16_t header; // Different from H264
66 };
67 struct Fragment {
68 Fragment(const uint8_t* buffer, size_t length);
69 explicit Fragment(const Fragment& fragment);
70 const uint8_t* buffer = nullptr;
71 size_t length = 0;
72 std::unique_ptr<rtc::Buffer> tmp_buffer;
73 };
74 struct PacketUnit {
75 PacketUnit(const Fragment& source_fragment,
76 bool first_fragment,
77 bool last_fragment,
78 bool aggregated,
79 uint16_t header)
80 : source_fragment(source_fragment),
81 first_fragment(first_fragment),
82 last_fragment(last_fragment),
83 aggregated(aggregated),
84 header(header) {}
85
86 const Fragment source_fragment;
87 bool first_fragment;
88 bool last_fragment;
89 bool aggregated;
90 uint16_t header;
91 };
92 typedef std::queue<Packet> PacketQueue;
93 std::deque<Fragment> input_fragments_;
94 std::queue<PacketUnit> packets_;
95
96 bool GeneratePackets(H265PacketizationMode packetization_mode);
97 bool PacketizeFu(size_t fragment_index);
98 int PacketizeAp(size_t fragment_index);
99 bool PacketizeSingleNalu(size_t fragment_index);
100
101 void NextAggregatePacket(RtpPacketToSend* rtp_packet, bool last);
102 void NextFragmentPacket(RtpPacketToSend* rtp_packet);
103
104 const PayloadSizeLimits limits_;
105 size_t num_packets_left_;
106
107 RTC_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(RtpPacketizerH265);
108};
109
110// Depacketizer for H.265.
111class VideoRtpDepacketizerH265 : public VideoRtpDepacketizer {
112 public:
113 virtual ~VideoRtpDepacketizerH265() {}
114
115 absl::optional<ParsedRtpPayload> Parse(
116 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer rtp_payload) override;
117
118 private:
119 bool ParseFuNalu(ParsedRtpPayload* parsed_payload,
120 const uint8_t* payload_data);
121 bool ProcessApOrSingleNalu(ParsedRtpPayload* parsed_payload,
122 const uint8_t* payload_data);
123
124 size_t offset_;
125 size_t length_;
126 std::unique_ptr<rtc::Buffer> modified_buffer_;
127};
128} // namespace webrtc
129#endif // WEBRTC_MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_FORMAT_H265_H_
